積.definition: to amass; to accumulate; to store up; (math.) product (the result of multiplication); (TCM) constipation; indigestion

積不相能.definition: (idiom) always at loggerheads; never able to agree with sb; unable to get on with sb

積代會.definition: (Cultural Revolution term) conference of activist representatives (abbr. for 積極分子代表大會|积极分子代表大会[ji1ji2 fen4zi3 dai4biao3 da4hui4])

積分.definition: integral (calculus); accumulated points (in sports, at school etc); total credits earned by student; bonus points in a benefit scheme

積分榜.definition: table of scores (in exams or sports league)

積勞成疾.definition: to accumulate work causes sickness (idiom); to fall ill from constant overwork

積土成山.definition: lit. piling up dirt eventually creates a mountain (idiom); fig. success is the cumulation of lots of small actions

積壓.definition: to pile up; to accumulate without being dealt with

積少成多.definition: (idiom) many little things add up to sth great; many little drops make an ocean

積年.definition: for a long time; over many years; old; advanced in age

積年累月.definition: year in, year out (idiom); (over) many years

積弊.definition: age-old (malpractice); long established (corrupt practices); deeply rooted (superstition)

積弱.definition: cumulative weakness; to decline (over time); degeneration

積德.definition: to accumulate merit; to do good; to give to charity; virtuous actions

積惡餘殃.definition: Accumulated evil will be repaid in suffering (idiom).

積攢.definition: to save bit by bit; to accumulate

積水.definition: to collect water; to be covered with water; to pond; accumulated water; ponding

積澱.definition: deposits accumulated over long periods; fig. valuable experience, accumulated wisdom

積疊.definition: to pile up layer upon layer

積石山保安族東鄉族撒拉族自治縣.pinyin: Ji1 shi2 shan1 Bao3 an1 zu2 Dong1 xiang1 zu2 Sa1 la1 zu2 Zi4 zhi4 xian4
積石山保安族東鄉族撒拉族自治縣.definition: Jishishan Bonan, Dongxiang and Salar Autonomous County in Linxia Hui Autonomous Prefecture 臨夏回族自治州|临夏回族自治州[Lin2 xia4 Hui2 zu2 Zi4 zhi4 zhou1], Gansu

積穀防饑.definition: storing grain against a famine; to lay sth by for a rainy day; also written 積穀防飢|积谷防饥

積習.definition: old habit (usually bad); inbred custom; deep-rooted practice

積習難改.definition: old habits are hard to change (idiom)

積聚.definition: to coalesce; to gather together; to amass

積肥.definition: to accumulate manure; to lay down compost

積草屯糧.definition: (idiom) to stockpile provisions in preparation for war

積蓄.definition: to save; to put aside; savings

積薪厝火.definition: to add fuel to the flames

積重難返.definition: ingrained habits are hard to overcome (idiom); bad old practices die hard

積金累玉.definition: to accumulate gold and jewels (idiom); prosperous

積非成是.definition: a wrong repeated becomes right (idiom); a lie or an error passed on for a long time may be taken for the truth

積食.definition: (of food) to retain in stomach due to indigestion (TCM)

積鬱.definition: (of gloomy thoughts etc) to smolder; to accumulate in one's mind; accumulated anxiety
